  "text": "Then R h \u2032 is smooth in the sense of [CITATION_1] , and R h is a smooth (1,1)-form on M . Similarly, S = \u03c0 * S \u2032 defines a global section of O M (D) vanishing along D and satisfies sup M S 2 h = 1. We then define the sequence of reference cone metrics,",
