    "14496968": {
      "title": "Singular K\u00e4hler-Einstein metrics",
      "abstract": "We study degenerate complex Monge-Amp\\`ere equations of the form $(\\omega+dd^c \\varphi)^n = e^{t \\varphi} \\mu$ where $\\omega$ is a big semi-positive form on a compact K\\\"ahler manifold $X$ of dimension $n$, $t \\in \\R^+$, and $\\mu=f\\omega^n$ is a positive measure with density $f\\in L^p(X,\\omega^n)$, $p>1$. We prove the existence and unicity of bounded $\\omega$-plurisubharmonic solutions. We also prove that the solution is continuous under a further technical condition. ::: In case $X$ is projective and $\\omega=\\psi^*\\omega'$, where $\\psi:X\\to V$ is a proper birational morphism to a normal projective variety, $[\\omega']\\in NS_{\\R} (V)$ is an ample class and $\\mu$ has only algebraic singularities, we prove that the solution is smooth in the regular locus of the equation. ::: We use these results to construct singular K\\\"ahler-Einstein metrics of non-positive curvature on projective klt pairs, in particular on canonical models of algebraic varieties of general type."
    }
  }
}